your customers and other internet users to view your site. It costs less than $10 a year to purchase a domain name. Domain names ending in  .com  or  .net  are the easiest to remember. When you sign up, you will need to make sure the domain name you selected is available, if not, try your next preferred choice.","Remember:"]},"id":"c0f74e3b-ce75-4116-b352-78d4bcc91439","type":"text"},{"data":{"items":["Keep the name and spelling simple","Connect your company name to your domain name"],"type":"ul"},"id":"a0bc1492-dde0-4534-84a2-a10f41cb1326","type":"list"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["2.\t<strong>Create a Functioning Website</strong>   Increase your percentage of returning customers by building a professional looking website. Online shoppers are used to ease, simplicity and speed. Building a professional looking site will do nothing for your business if it is not user-friendly and easy to navigate, users will not take extra time to figure it out, they will move on to a different site.","Decide what you like in other websites. Look at some of your favorite websites and learn from them. You can also search  worst websites ever  and learn from the mistakes of others. After seeing some of the good and bad examples, it is easy to understand the fundamental design keys that will keep your customers browsing your site. Help users know your site is safe and secure; a professional looking design with little clutter and easy to use tabs, icons and links are the essence of ease and professionalism. Your customer will stay on your site if they can easily navigate their way around; make sure links and tabs are set up so that the user can find what they need to move forward and take a step back as needed.","Keys to keep in mind:"]},"id":"431f6125-e4dc-4db0-aeb9-72469b1a62c9","type":"text"},{"data":{"items":["Professional, uncluttered","Easy to use navigation"],"type":"ul"},"id":"bfac1c92-18a0-499f-9092-bfa91ce59c09","type":"list"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["3.\t<strong>Advertise</strong>   There are many ways and opportunities for you to advertise your business online. Creating a Facebook fan page is one of the many tools you can use to incorporate your business advertising with the hype and popularity of social networking. A more expensive but also productive source of advertising is purchasing banner ads. A banner ad is a more extensive form of advertising because you will need to design an ad and find relevant or popular sites for placing them.","Another popular form of advertising is e-mail lists. Begin by compiling a list of e-mails and providing your customers with the option to add their e-mail on your site to receive updates on the business, promotions, giveaways or specials you market. Advertise tactfully with professional ads and no amount of advertising will be &#34;too much.&#34; The goal is to get your business into the public eye and mind.","Simple and easy starting points:"]},"id":"926112ad-6eca-4c65-ae3c-d98535235ce5","type":"text"},{"data":{"items":["Social Networking","Banner Ads","E-mail List"],"type":"ul"},"id":"0cd466a8-1312-4d04-9450-a265772fa9d0","type":"list"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["4.\t<strong>Search Engine Optimization (SEO)</strong>   Every day millions of internet users search the web for products and services that they want or need. The search engines find up-to-date data and create a copy of visited pages for later processing. Adding key words or phrases to your site will increase the number of times your company site attracts the search engines to your domain. Research SEO keywords to find more information on how to get your company recognized.","5.\t<strong>Customer Satisfaction</strong>   Customer satisfaction will make or break a company reputation and business. Keep the quality of your work high and make sure your customer gets the attention and service they need to keep them coming back for more. The customers will keep you in business and help your business grow if they get the quality product and service they a